05221nam a22009255i 9783110253481DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20122012gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)853262662  a97831102534817 a10.1515/97831102534812doi  a(DE-B1597)123434  a(OCoLC)847594180  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aREL0061002bisacsh1 aHartvigsen, Kirsten Marie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aPrepare the Way of the Lord :bTowards a Cognitive Poetic Analysis of Audience Involvement with Characters and Events in the Markan World /cKirsten Marie Hartvigsen. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2012] 4c©2012  a1 online resource (621 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBeihefte zur Zeitschrift für die neutestamentliche Wissenschaft ,x0171-6441 ;v1800 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis study analyzes an oral performance of the entire Gospel of Mark, with emphasis on involvement with characters and events, the emotional effects of such involvement, and how these processes maintain or shape the identity of those who hear the Gospel. Insights from cognitive poetics and psychonarratology are employed to illuminate the complex, cognitive processes that take place when audience members experience an oral performance of the Gospel. Consequently, this study expands previous research on the Gospel of Mark which was conducted on the basis of narrative criticism, orality criticism, and performance criticism by including cognitive aspects. Cognitive poetics and psychonarratology have to my knowledge not been extensively employed to illuminate an oral performance of the Gospel of Mark previously. This investigation provides: (1) An original, coherent theoretical and methodological framework; (2) An analysis of mechanisms which promote involvement with characters and events in the Markan narrative; (3) An examination of the prospective emotional effects of such involvement; (4) Reflections on the potential of these mechanisms with regard to identity maintenance or formation through cultural memory; (5) A cognitive poetic commentary on the entire Gospel of Mark.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aKognitive Poetik. 4aKulturelles Gedächtnis. 4aMarkusevangelium. 4aMündliche Überlieferung. 4aPoetik der Rezeption. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aCognitive Poetics.  aCultural Memory.  aGospel of Mark.  aOral Performance.  aPoetics of Reception.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUDAISM, RELIGION  2012z978311029384508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE,RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2012z9783110288957oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311025347440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025348140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110253481423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110253481/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-029384-5  E-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUDAISM, RELIGION  2012b2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  